{
  "name": "bistable_motif",
  "description": "Bistable memory unit — 1-bit digital latch. Three CH neurons (a=0, c=-65, d=0) in a recurrent ring with self-excitation. The 'digital cheat': a=0 freezes recovery variable u at -13 forever; c=-65 resets voltage below the unstable fixed point (-58.2) so the OFF state is truly stable; d=0 means no recovery kick. ON state sustained by ring (w=12, d=1) + self-loops (w=8, d=2). OFF state stable because tonic 2.5 alone gives dv/dt=-0.5 at v=-65. RS gate triggers all three ON. FS kill breaks the ring — once any cycle is suppressed, all neurons fall to v=-66.8 and stay silent.",
  "nodes": [
    {"id": 0, "type": "CH", "x": 0.0, "z": 0.0, "params": {"a": 0.0, "c": -65.0, "d": 0.0}},
    {"id": 1, "type": "CH", "x": 2.0, "z": 1.0, "params": {"a": 0.0, "c": -65.0, "d": 0.0}},
    {"id": 2, "type": "CH", "x": 1.0, "z": -1.0, "params": {"a": 0.0, "c": -65.0, "d": 0.0}},
    {"id": 3, "type": "RS", "x": 1.0, "z": -3.0},
    {"id": 4, "type": "FS", "x": 1.0, "z": 3.0}
  ],
  "paths": [
